Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Ministerial to Advance Religious Freedom, emphasizing the United States' commitment to promoting religious freedom both domestically and abroad. He highlighted the importance of religious freedom in maintaining peace and security and called out countries that violate this freedom, such as China, North Korea, Russia, and Iran. Pence also announced the establishment of the Genocide Recovery and Persecution Response Program, which aims to provide aid to persecuted religious communities, and the International Religious Freedom Fund, which will support those fighting for religious freedom. He ended his speech by urging the release of American pastor Andrew Brunson, who has been detained in Turkey.